    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-09-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.032/4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 948.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-09-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 19, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit to the Department
                    clippings from the Mexican Herald and El Diario Oficial, of this city containing
                    the text in English and Spanish of the message read by President de la Barra on
                    the occasion of the opening of the first period of the Mexican Congress, on the
                    16th instant, for the fiscal year 1911–1912.<note n="1" xml:id="d1341fn1"
                        >Printed in <ref target="frus1911#pg_517">For. Rel. 1911, p.
                        517</ref>.</note> The attention of the Department is especially called to
                    that portion of the message which relates to the attitude of the Mexican
                    Government concerning the payment of claims growing out of the recent
                    Revolution.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
